    "### Find Optimum Number of clusters in GMM\n", 
    "\n", 
    "1. Iterate over all possible values for n_components, and covariance type\n", 
    "2. Store the BIC Score, n_components, and covariance type\n", 
    "3. Use catplot to visualise the results. Choose n_components, and covariance type accordingly"

    "BIC_score = []\n", 
    "n = []\n", 
    "types = []\n", 
    "\n", 
    "for k in range(1,11):\n", 
    "    for type in [\"spherical\", \"tied\", \"diag\", \"full\"]:\n", 
    "        gmm = GaussianMixture(n_components=k, random_state=42, covariance_type=type)\n", 
    "        gmm.fit(df2)\n", 
    "        BIC_score.append(gmm.bic(df2))\n", 
    "        n.append(k)\n", 
    "        types.append(type)\n", 
    "\n", 
    "result = pd.DataFrame()\n", 
    "result['n_components'] = n\n", 
    "result['covariance_type'] = types\n",

    "### Anomaly Detection in GMM\n", 
    "1. Fit the GMM to Your Data\n", 
    "2. Calculate the Log-Likelihood of Each Data Point\n", 
    "3. Determine the Threshold for Anomaly Detection:\n", 
    "        * Assume it's 5 percentile here\n", 
    "4. Flag anomalies\n", 
    "        * Any data point with a log-likelihood below this threshold is flagged as an anomaly." 
   ],

    "def detect_anomalies(df2, gmm):\n", 
    "    \"\"\"\n", 
    "        Input: \n", 
    "            df2 - Pandas Dataframe\n", 
    "            gmm - Optimal model   \n", 
    "        Output: \n", 
    "            anomalies - A dataframe containing anomalies  \n", 
    "    \"\"\"\n", 
    "    log_likelihoods = gmm.score_samples(df2)\n", 
    "    threshold = np.percentile(log_likelihoods, 5) # Set threshold at 5th percentile\n", 
    "    anomalies = df2[log_likelihoods < threshold]  # Filter data points below the threshold\n", 
    "    return anomalies" 
   ],
